defaultBetter Business FinancedefaultBetter Business Finance (BBF) provides impartial information and support to business customers looking to raise finance. The BBF
default is supported by the BBA in conjunction with some of our members and has been created to bring to life the recommendations of the
default&#xa0;
defaultBusiness 
defaultFinance Taskforce
default. The BBF has three core themes at its heart: improving customer relationships; improving access to finance;
default&#xa0;
defaultas well as
default improving information and transparency. It
default&#xa0;
defaultincludes supporting businesses through 
defaultmentoring; 
defaultthe introduction of an 
defaultindependently monitored appeals process for finance applications and providing guidance to UK businesses on how to export abroad or pitch to a bank when seeking finance. 
default&#xa0;
defaultThe BBF and its initiatives are gaining good traction with businesses generally but 
defaultwe acknowledge awareness of the mentoring and appeals support in Northern Ireland, as well as the support tools available for businesses such as mentorsme.co.uk, betterbusinessfinance.co.uk and businessfinanceforyou.co.uk, are not as extensive as we would 
defaulthave hoped. 
default&#xa0;
defaultTo this end, we are working with the banks and the Northern Ireland Chambers of Commerce upon how we can further invigorate the mentoring scheme and with Professor Russel Griggs, with the CBI, and more generally the Ulster Business School, up
defaulton how the appeals process and support tools are more widely known. Further detail
defaults
default are 
defaultoutlined below
